As an addendum:
I've opened a bug with Puppet after determining this is specifically an issue with a Puppet supplied ruby file, webrick.rb.

The issue occurs in 
/usr/local/lib/ruby/site_ruby/2.3/puppet/network/http/webrick.rb:32 {
sock.accept
}

If we patch this locally to: {
sock.accept_nonblock
}
it would resolve the issue on our end, until Puppet does the same upstream.

Puppet bug is open at:
https://tickets.puppetlabs.com/browse/PUP-8297
